The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) on Monday in Kaduna opened a three-day workshop for electoral officers responsible for monitoring elections and political parties. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that INEC is being supported by the European Centre for Electoral Support (ECES) to train the workers on Party Management and Administration ahead of 2023 polls. INEC’s Director of Election and Party Monitoring, Mr. Aminu Idris, announced at the opening of the workshop that the participants were drawn from the commission’s offices in the 19 northern states. Idris said the workshop was meant to build the capacity of the workers to effectively monitor political parties to improve the electoral process ahead of 2023 general polls.